This article is a fact sheet from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, released on May 19, 2011. It discusses the new approach of the United States towards promoting democratic reform, economic development, and peace and security in the Middle East and North Africa. The article emphasizes the commitment to core principles such as opposing violence and repression, supporting universal rights, and promoting political and economic change in the region. It also highlights specific actions and support for countries like Bahrain, Egypt, Jordan, Libya, Morocco, Syria, Tunisia, and Yemen. The article further discusses the focus on economic development, including support for economic policy formulation, stability, modernization, and trade integration and investment. It also addresses the commitment to promoting peace and security, ending the combat mission in Iraq, building a strategic partnership, and focusing on Al Qa`ida. The article concludes by highlighting the importance of political change and standing up for universal rights in Iran.